Subject: [PATCH] arm64: dts: apple: t600x-j314-j316: Fix HDMI resume issue

Keep both ATC3 power domains always-on to fix HDMI suspend/resume issues
on MacBook Pro (14/16-inch, 2021). The ps_atc3_common domain alone is not
sufficient - the ps_atc3_usb_aon domain also needs to stay powered for
proper HDMI resume functionality.


---
 arch/arm64/boot/dts/apple/t600x-j314-j316.dtsi | 3 ++-
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/apple/t600x-j314-j316.dtsi b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/apple/t600x-j314-j316.dtsi
index 8d030df13bf5..d230ffc09f8c 100644
--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/apple/t600x-j314-j316.dtsi
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/apple/t600x-j314-j316.dtsi
@@ -483,9 +483,10 @@ dwc3_2_ss: endpoint {
 /*
  * ps_atc3_usb_aon power-domain is always-on to keep dwc3 working over suspend.
  * atc3 is used exclusively for the DP-to-HDMI so do not keep this always on.
+ * TODO: Temporarily keeping both power domains always-on for HDMI resume fix
  */
 &ps_atc3_usb_aon {
-	/delete-property/ apple,always-on;
+	/* /delete-property/ apple,always-on; */
 };
 
 /* ATC3 is used for DisplayPort -> HDMI only */
-- 
2.43.0
